# Dreamscroll production API requests
#
# 1) Generate or refresh token file:
#    ./prod-api-token.sh
#    (prompts for username + hidden password)
#
# 2) This file reads `PROD_API_TOKEN` from `.env` in this same folder (`src/rest/.env`).
#    `prod-api-token.sh` writes that file for you, and it is gitignored.

@token = {{$dotenv PROD_API_TOKEN}}

###
GET https://dreamscroll.ai/api/dummy
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
GET https://dreamscroll.ai/api/timeline
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
GET https://dreamscroll.ai/api/captures?id=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
GET https://dreamscroll.ai/api/captures
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
fail

###
POST https://dreamscroll.ai/api/captures/import
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----dreamscrollboundary

------dreamscrollboundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="created_at"

2024-01-02T03:04:05Z
------dreamscrollboundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="capture.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./sample.jpg
------dreamscrollboundary--

###
# Returns 204 No Content on success
DELETE https://dreamscroll.ai/api/captures/605
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Requires an admin JWT token
POST https://dreamscroll.ai/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "mdr3",
    "password": ,
    "email": 
}
